column5: I finally made it out Friday, Oct. 21 and water temps were 47-49. Muskies did not cooperate though!
Anyone out on LOTW northern region and know current water temps? Interested in Kenora, Ptarmigan, CrowRock and Wiley point area....

We have been up at Flag Island since 9/30. Have not been as far north as you have requested but since there were no other responses I thought I would let you know that the last few days have been very cold and windy. The temp at Young's Bay yesterday was 43 degrees. This is a drop of at least 10 degrees since we arrived up here. Best wishes, T
Previous posts have shown various sites that show current temps at various places. Cannot find those posts but did find this.https://lakemonster.com/lake/MN/Lake...emperature-307
Still to warm to think about iceshacks........Lol.
It's walk on ice only now!travel at your own risk!!
Don't be jumping the gun yet.Ways to go.-6c just puts a skim on.
Just bring ice pixs looks like a go!
Yup..lol. Hoping to get another musky fishing trip in!!!
It was 42 yesterday in morson, but temps are going to be warming quite a bit over the next 5 days.
